i/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/resume.go`)\\n\\nThe `resume` command does the following:\\n\\n1. **Branch Switching** (lines 61-121)\\n   - Checks if branch exists locally; if not, asks to fetch from origin\\n   - Performs git checkout to the target branch\\n   - Handles uncommitted changes validation\\n\\n2. **Checkpoint Discovery** (lines 123-173)\\n   - Calls `findBranchCheckpoint()` to locate a commit with `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer\\n   - Walks commit history from HEAD, looking **only for commits unique to the branch** (not on main/master)\\n   - Distinguishes between merge commits (ignored) and regular branch work commits\\n   - Returns the most recent commit with a checkpoint trailer\\n\\n3. **Metadata Branch Lookup** (lines 158-173)\\n   - Tries to read checkpoint metadata from local `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch\\n   - Falls back to checking remote if local metadata doesn't exist\\n   - Auto-fetches remote metadata if available\\n\\n4. **Session Restoration** (lines 359-472)\\n   - Calls `strat.RestoreLogsOnly()` to restore session logs from checkpoint\\n   - Supports **multi-session checkpoints** (multiple sessions in one checkpoint)\\n   - Sorts sessions by creation time to show most recent as primary\\n   - Prints appropriate resume commands for each session\\n\\n### **2. CHECKPOINT SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE**\\n\\n#### **Shadow Branches** (`entire/<commit[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>`)\\n\\nThe naming is constructed in `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/checkpoint/temporary.go`:\\n\\n```\\nfunc ShadowBranchNameForCommit(baseCommit, worktreeID string) string:\\n  - commitPart := baseCommit[:7]  (first 7 chars of commit hash)\\n  - worktreeHash := HashWorktreeID(worktreeID)[:6]  (SHA256 hash truncated to 6 chars)\\n  - Format: \\\"entire/<commit-prefix>-<worktree-hash>\\\"\\n```\\n\\n**Purpose**: Temporary checkpoints are stored on shadow branches, one branch per base commit + worktree combination. This allows:\\n- Multiple concurrent sessions to share the same shadow branch (checkpoints interleave)\\n- Each git worktree to have separate shadow branches (prevents conflicts)\\n- Session state tracking in `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json`\\n\\n#### **Metadata Branch** (`entire/checkpoints/v1`)\\n\\nPermanent, sharded checkpoint metadata storage:\\n```\\n<checkpoint_id[:2]>/<checkpoint_id[2:]>/\\n├── metadata.json        # CheckpointSummary (aggregated stats)\\n├── 0/                   # First session (0-based folder indexing)\\n│   ├── metadata.json    # Session-specific metadata\\n│   ├── full.jsonl       # Session transcript\\n│   ├── prompt.txt       # User prompts\\n│   ├── context.md       # Generated context\\n│   └── tasks/<tool-use-id>/  # Task checkpoints\\n├── 1/                   # Second session (if multi-session checkpoint)\\n│   ├── metadata.json\\n│   └── ...\\n```\\n\\n**Checkpoint ID**: 12 hex characters (random, generated fresh per checkpoint via `id.Generate()`)\\n\\n### **3. COMMIT LINKING: THE ENTIRE-CHECKPOINT TRAILER**\\n\\nLocated in `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/trailers/trailers.go`:\\n\\n**Format**: `Entire-Checkpoint: <12-hex-checkpoint-id>`\\n\\n**Lifecycle**:\\n1. **PrepareCommitMsg Hook** (lines 219-388 of `manual_commit_hooks.go`):\\n   - Generates fresh 12-hex checkpoint ID via `id.Generate()`\\n   - Adds trailer to commit message if session has new content to condense\\n   - Skipped for merge/squash/rebase operations\\n   - User can remove trailer before committing (opt-out mechanism)\\n\\n2. **PostCommit Hook** (lines 623-731 of `manual_commit_hooks.go`):\\n   - Checks for `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer in commit message\\n   - If found, triggers condensation via `CondenseSession()`\\n   - Extracts session data from shadow branch\\n   - Writes to `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch\\n\\n3. **Trailer Persistence**:\\n   - The trailer survives git amend (restored from `LastCheckpointID` in session state)\\n   - Trailer is preserved through rebase/cherry-pick (since it's in commit message)\\n\\n### **4. SESSION STATE** (`.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json`)\\n\\nDefined in `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go`:\\n\\n**Key Fields**:\\n\\n| Field | Purpose |\\n|-------|---------|\\n| `SessionID` | Unique identifier (UUID with date prefix) |\\n| `BaseCommit` | Current shadow branch base commit hash; **updated after pull/rebase** |\\n| `AttributionBaseCommit` | Original base commit for attribution (doesn't change on migration) |\\n| `WorktreeID` | Internal git worktree identifier (empty for main, stable for linked worktrees) |\\n| `Phase` | Session lifecycle state (ACTIVE, IDLE, ENDED) |\\n| `FilesTouched` | Accumulates files modified across entire session (not cleared at new prompts) |\\n| `LastCheckpointID` | Most recent checkpoint ID (used to restore trailer on amend) |\\n| `TurnID` | Unique ID for current agent turn (regenerated at each new prompt) |\\n| `TurnCheckpointIDs` | Checkpoint IDs created during current turn (cleared after turn ends) |\\n\\n### **5. CONDENSATION FLOW**\\n\\nLocated in `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`:\\n\\n**CondenseSession() Process** (lines 113-299):\\n\\n1. **Extract Session Data**:\\n   - From shadow branch (if exists) or live transcript (mid-session commit)\\n   - Reads entire transcript up to current point\\n   - Pulls metadata from `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/` directory\\n   - Filters files to only those committed in this commit (via `committedFiles` set)\\n\\n2. **Attribution Calculation**:\\n   - Compares base commit tree vs agent's changes\\n   - Determines which lines were agent vs user changes\\n   - Stored as `InitialAttribution` in checkpoint metadata\\n\\n3. **Write to Metadata Branch**:\\n   - Uses `checkpoint.GitStore.WriteCommitted()`\\n   - Writes to sharded path: `<id[:2]>/<id[2:]>/`\\n   - Creates new commit on `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n\\n4. **Update Session State**:\\n   - `LastCheckpointID` = new checkpoint ID\\n   - `FilesTouched` = carried-forward files (from content-aware check)\\n   - `BaseCommit` = updated if HEAD changed\\n   - `CheckpointTranscriptStart` = reset to 0\\n\\n### **6. CRITICAL INSIGHT: SQUASH MERGE SCENARIO**\\n\\nAfter a squash merge, here's what happens:\\n\\n**Before Merge**:\\n- Feature branch has 3 commits: C1, C2, C3\\n- Each has `Entire-Checkpoint: ID1`, `ID2`, `ID3` trailers\\n- Each links to metadata on `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n- Shadow branch: `entire/<commit-C1>-<worktreeHash>`\\n\\n**After Squash Merge to Main**:\\n- Main has new commit CM (squashed combination)\\n- Old branch commits C1, C2, C3 still exist as dangling commits in reflog\\n- **The `Entire-Checkpoint` trailers are PRESERVED** in commit message of CM (if squash message includes all trailers)\\n- OR **Trailers are LOST** if user customizes squash message\\n\\n**What Breaks**:\\n1. Shadow branch name `entire/<commit-C1>-...` becomes invalid (C1 is no longer the base of any active branch)\\n2. When user tries to `entire resume` on squashed commit:\\n   - `findBranchCheckpoint()` looks for commits unique to squashed branch (if already merged)\\n   - If user switches to CM's branch, it won't find the checkpoint (it's on a different commit hash)\\n   - Session state files for the old sessions still exist in `.git/entire-sessions/`\\n\\n### **7. FILES TO UNDERSTAND FOR SQUASH-MERGE FIX**\\n\\n**Critical Files**:\\n\\n1. **`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`** (lines 219-388)\\n   - PrepareCommitMsg: Where trailer is added\\n   - PostCommit: Where condensation is triggered\\n   - Key: Need to detect squash scenario and preserve/restore trailer\\n\\n2. **`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`** (lines 113-299)\\n   - CondenseSession: Where metadata is written\\n   - Key: May need to handle merged sessions\\n\\n3. **`cmd/entire/cli/resume.go`** (lines 123-173)\\n   - findBranchCheckpoint: Checkpoint discovery logic\\n   - Key: May need to search more broadly for checkpoints