otely. The real challenge is that the metadata still knows about those checkpoints under the deleted branch name, so the approach needs to handle looking up checkpoints by branch name in the metadata even when that branch no longer exists. The core issue is that after a squash merge to main and deleting the feature branch, the checkpoints vanish because the squash commit itself doesn't carry the checkpoint trailers—they only exist in the metadata branch tied to the original branch name. I need to make checkpoints discoverable through the metadata branch as a fallback, and also consider how the dashboard walks commits to find checkpoints, since it might miss them entirely when the branch is gone.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":2598,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":75327,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":2598},\"output_tokens\":8,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYXCNHPntRqK3iMT3WxUy\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"588723dc-c5c1-445c-b0ca-ff7c7425ecfe\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T19:01:34.557Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"588723dc-c5c1-445c-b0ca-ff7c7425ecfe\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"3f1e469e-cc70-4a20-80b9-4d66e624b432\",\"version\":\"2.1.52\",\"gitBranch\":\"squash-merge-resume\",\"slug\":\"sparkling-petting-kahn\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_019Xdwj8d53sFzwVbkPr3nP3\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good, I now have a thorough understanding of the system. Let me ask the next clarifying question.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":2598,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":75327,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_t