eo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYXPzBB2PyJqMYtNUy5c4\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"9c01f0d0-825c-4f97-b74e-9b4f595dd2e9\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T21:33:30.776Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"9c01f0d0-825c-4f97-b74e-9b4f595dd2e9\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"3f1e469e-cc70-4a20-80b9-4d66e624b432\",\"version\":\"2.1.52\",\"gitBranch\":\"squash-merge-resume\",\"slug\":\"sparkling-petting-kahn\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Read\",\"command\":\"callback\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01TbTSzuzRap6j6DsnuC1MMo\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01TbTSzuzRap6j6DsnuC1MMo\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T21:33:30.808Z\",\"uuid\":\"a5c9eda2-797b-4785-812d-be64694e7604\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"9c01f0d0-825c-4f97-b74e-9b4f595dd2e9\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"3f1e469e-cc70-4a20-80b9-4d66e624b432\",\"version\":\"2.1.52\",\"gitBranch\":\"squash-merge-resume\",\"slug\":\"sparkling-petting-kahn\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01TbTSzuzRap6j6DsnuC1MMo\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Squash Merge Resume Support\\n     2→\\n     3→## Problem\\n     4→\\n     5→When a feature branch is squash-merged into main (via GitHub PR), the squash commit message contains all individual commit messages, including their `Entire-Checkpoint` trailers. However, `entire resume` only parses the first trailer, so only one of potentially many sessions is restored.\\n     6→\\n     7→Customer-reported reproduction:\\n     8→1. Work on feature branch with Entire sessions, creating multiple commits with checkpoints\\n     9→2. Squash-merge PR to main\\n    10→3. `entire resume main` only finds the first checkpoint; remaining sessions are invisible\\n    11→4. Deleting the feature branch makes the original per-commit checkpoints unreachable\\n    12→\\n    13→Example squash commit message from GitHub:\\n    14→```\\n    15→Soph/test branch (#2)\\n    16→* random_letter script\\n    17→\\n    18→Entire-Checkpoint: 0aa0814d9839\\n    19→\\n    20→* random color\\n    21→\\n    22→Entire-Checkpoint: 33fb587b6fbb\\n    23→```\\n    24→\\n    25→## Design\\n    26→\\n    27→### Approach: Multi-checkpoint parsing in the resume flow\\n    28→\\n    29→The fix is localized to trailer parsing and the resume command. No changes to condensation, hooks, or the checkpoint storage format.\\n    30→\\n    31→### 1. Trailer Parsing (`trailers/trailers.go`)\\n    32→\\n    33→Add `ParseAllCheckpoints()` following the existing `ParseAllSessions()` pattern:\\n    34→- Uses `FindAllStringSubmatch` instead of `FindStringSubmatch`\\n    35→- Deduplicates checkpoint IDs while preserving order\\n    36→- Returns `[]checkpointID.CheckpointID`\\n    37→\\n    38→The existing `ParseCheckpoint()` (single-match) remains unchanged for callers that only need one.\\n    39→\\n    40→### 2. Checkpoint Discovery (`resume.go`)\\n    41→\\n    42→Change `branchCheckpointResult.checkpointID` (single) to `checkpointIDs` (slice).\\n    43→\\n    44→Update `findBranchCheckpoint` and `findCheckpointInHistory`:\\n    45→- Use `ParseAllCheckpoints()` instead of `ParseCheckpoint()`\\n    46→- The HEAD fast-path and history walk both collect all IDs from the first matching commit\\n    47→- Empty-check becomes `len(result.checkpointIDs) == 0`\\n    48→\\n    49→### 3. Resume Flow (`resume.go`)\\n    50→\\n    51→Single-checkpoint path (common case) stays identical — no behavior change. When `len(checkpointIDs) == 1`, the existing `resumeSession` flow is used.\\n    52→\\n    53→New `resumeMultipleCheckpoints` function for squash merge commits:\\n    54→1. Gets metadata branch tree (with remote fallback)\\n    55→2. Loops over checkpoint IDs, calling `ReadCheckpointMetadata` + `strat.RestoreLogsOnly` for each\\n    56→3. Skips checkpoints whose metadata isn't available (best-effort)\\n    57→4. Aggregates all restored sessions into a single slice\\n    58→5. Sorts by `CreatedAt` and displays resume commands\\n    59→\\n    60→Output matches existing multi-session format:\\n    61→```\\n    62→Restored 2 sessions. To continue, run:\\n    63→  claude --resume abc123  # implement random_letter script\\n    64→  claude --resume def456  # add random color (most recent)\\n    65→```\\n    66→\\n    67→## Scope\\n    68→\\n    69→### In scope\\n    70→- `trailers/trailers.go` — new `ParseAllCheckpoints()` function\\n    71→- `resume.go` — updated `branchCheckpointResult`, `findBranchCheckpoint`, `findCheckpointInHistory`, new `resumeMultipleCheckpoints`\\n    72→- Tests for all changed code\\n    73→\\n    74→### Out of scope\\n    75→- Dashboard visibility (separate concern)\\n    76→- Handling stripped/customized squash commit messages (best-effort: we work with available trailers)\\n    77→- Branch-not-found error messaging (keep existing behavior)\\n    78→- Changes to condensation, hooks, or checkpoint storage format\\n    79→\\n    80→## Edge Cases\\n    81→\\n    82→- **User customizes squash message and removes trailers**: Best effort — we can only find what's there. Same behavior as today (no checkpoint found).\\n    83→- **Some checkpoint metadata missing**: Skip those checkpoints, restore what we can.\\n    84→- **Single checkpoint in squash commit**: Falls through to existing single-checkpoint path, no behavior change.\\n    85→- **Non-squash commits**: Always have 0 or 1 trailer, existing behavior preserved.\\n    86→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"9537a591-291a-4052-82c9-0ddd86a9d709\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T21:33:30.807Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/docs/plans/2026-02-26-squash-merge-resume-design.md\",\"content\":\"# Squash Merge Resume Support\\n\\n## Problem\\n\\nWhen a feature branch is squash-merged into main (via GitHub PR), the squash commit message contains all individual commit messages, including their `Entire-Checkpoint` trailers. However, `entire resume` only parses the first trailer, so only one of potentially many sessions is restored.\\n\\nCustomer-reported reproduction:\\n1. Work on feature branch with Entire sessions, creating multiple commits with checkpoints\\n2. Squash-merge PR to main\\n3. `entire resume main` only finds the first checkpoint; remaining sessions are invisible\\n4. Deleting the feature branch makes the original per-commit checkpoints unreachable\\n\\nExample squash commit message from GitHub:\\n```\\nSoph/test branch (#2)\\n* random_letter script\\n\\nEntire-Checkpoint: 0aa0814d9839\\n\\n* random color\\n\\nEntire-Checkpoint: 33fb587b6fbb\\n```\\n\\n## Design\\n\\n### Approach: Multi-checkpoint parsing in the resume flow\\n\\nThe fix is localized to trailer parsing and the resume command. No changes to condensation, hooks, or the checkpoint storage format.\\n\\n### 1. Trailer Parsing (`trailers/trailers.go`)\\n\\nAdd `ParseAllCheckpoints()` following the existing `ParseAllSessions()` pattern:\\n- Uses `FindAllStringSubmatch` instead of `FindStringSubmatch`\\n- Deduplicates checkpoint IDs while preserving order\\n- Returns `[]checkpointID.CheckpointID`\\n\\nThe existing `ParseCheckpoint()` (single-match) remains unchanged for callers that only need one.\\n\\n### 2. Checkpoint Discovery (`resume.go`)\\n\\nChange `branchCheckpointResult.checkpointID` (single) to `checkpointIDs` (slice).\\n\\nUpdate `findBranchCheckpoint` and `findCheckpointInHistory`:\\n- Use `ParseAllCheckpoints()` instead of `ParseCheckpoint()`\\n- The HEAD fast-path and history walk both collect all IDs from the first matching commit\\n- Empty-check becomes `len(result.checkpointIDs) == 0`\\n\\n### 3. Resume Flow (`resume.go`)\\n\\nSingle-checkpoint path (common case) stays identical — no behavior change. When `len(checkpointIDs) == 1`, the existing `resumeSession` flow is used.\\n\\nNew `resumeMultipleCheckpoints` function for squash merge commits:\\n1. Gets metadata branch tree (with remote fallback)\\n2. Loops over checkpoint IDs, calling `ReadCheckpointMetadata` + `strat.RestoreLogsOnly` for each\\n3. Skips checkpoints whose metadata isn't available (best-effort)\\n4. Aggregates all restored sessions into a single slice\\n5. Sorts by `CreatedAt` and displays resume commands\\n\\nOutput matches existing multi-session format:\\n```\\nRestored 2 sessions. To continue, run:\\n  claude --resume abc123  # implement random_letter script\\n  claude --resume def456  # add random color (most recent)\\n```\\n\\n## Scope\\n\\n### In scope\\n- `trailers/trailers.go` — new `ParseAllCheckpoints()` function\\n- `resume.go` — updated `branchCheckpointResult`, `findBranchCheckpoint`, `findCheckpointInHistory`, new `resumeMultipleCheckpoints`\\n- Tests for all changed code\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n- Dashboard visibility (separate concern)\\n- Handling stripped/customized squash commit messages (best-effort: we work with available trailers)\\n- Branch-not-found error messaging (keep existing behavior)\\n- Changes to condensation, hooks, or checkpoint storage format\\n\\n## Edge Cases\\n\\n- **User customizes squash message and removes trailers**: Best effort — we can only find what's there. Same behavior as today (no checkpoint found).\\n- **Some checkpoint metadata missing**: Skip those checkpoints, restore what we can.\\n- **Single checkpoint in squash commit**: Falls through to existing single-checkpoint path, no behavior change.\\n- **Non-squash commits**: Always have 0 or 1 trailer, existing behavior preserved.\\n\",\"numLines\":86,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":86}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"9c01f0d0-825c-4f97-b74e-9b4f595dd2e9\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"9537a591-291a-4052-82c9-0ddd86a9d709\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"3f1e469e-cc70-4a20-80b9-4d66e624b432\",\"version\":\"2.1.52\",\"gitBranch\":\"squash-merge-resume\",\"slug\":\"sparkling-petting-kahn\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01WLhTRzwP2vfXF58Nfjm9Xx\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01QMRZ1XYPE5VqGV2V4aYdZd\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/trailers/trailers.go\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1092,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":92062,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1092},\"output_tokens\":2,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYXPzBB2PyJqMYtNUy5c4\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"e2e212bf-e8dd-44a3-8210-49e41d13853f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T21:33:31.286Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"e2e212bf-e8dd-44a3-8210-49e41d13853f\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"3f1e469e-cc70-4a20-80b9-4d66e624b432\",\"version\":\"2.1.52\",\"gitBranch\":\"squash-merge-resume\",\"slug\":\"sparkling-petting-kahn\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Read\",\"command\":\"callback\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01QMRZ1XYPE5VqGV2V4aYdZd\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01QMRZ1XYPE5VqGV2V4aYdZd\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T21:33:31.321Z\",\"uuid\":\"88987979-9909-45db-b423-124527d00048\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"e2e212bf-e8dd-44a3-8210-49e41d13853f\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"3f1e469e-cc70-4a20-80b9-4d66e624b432\",\"version\":\"2.1.52\",\"gitBranch\":\"squash-merge-resume\",\"slug\":\"sparkling-petting-kahn\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01QMRZ1XYPE5VqGV2V4aYdZd\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→// Package trailers provides parsing and formatting for Entire commit message trailers.\\n     2→// Trailers are key-value metadata appended to git commit messages following the\\n     3→// git trailer convention (key: value format after a blank line).\\n     4→package trailers\\n     5→\\n     6→import (\\n     7→\\t\\\"fmt\\\"\\n     8→\\t\\\"regexp\\\"\\n     9→\\t\\\"strings\\\"\\n    10→\\n    11→\\tcheckpointID \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/id\\\"\\n    12→)\\n    13→\\n    14→// Trailer key constants used in commit messages.\\n    15→const (\\n    16→\\t// MetadataTrailerKey points to the metadata directory within a commit tree.\\n    17→\\tMetadataTrailerKey = \\\"Entire-Metadata\\\"\\n    18→\\n    19→\\t// MetadataTaskTrailerKey points to the task metadata directory for subagent checkpoints.\\n    20→\\tMetadataTaskTrailerKey = \\\"Entire-Metadata-Task\\\"\\n    21→\\n    22→\\t// StrategyTrailerKey indicates which strategy created the commit.\\n    23→\\tStrategyTrailerKey = \\\"Entire-Strategy\\\"\\n    24→\\n    25→\\t// BaseCommitTrailerKey links shadow commits to their base code commit.\\n    26→\\tBaseCommitTrailerKey = \\\"Base-Commit\\\"\\n    27→\\n    28→\\t// SessionTrailerKey identifies which session created a commit.\\n    29→\\tSessionTrailerKey = \\\"Entire-Session\\\"\\n    30→\\n    31→\\t// CondensationTrailerKey identifies the condensation ID for a commit (legacy).\\n    32→\\tCondensationTrailerKey = \\\"Entire-Condensation\\\"\\n    33→\\n    34→\\t// SourceRefTrailerKey links code commits to their metadata on a shadow/metadata branch.\\n    35→\\t// Format: \\\"<branch>@<commit-hash>\\\" e.g. \\\"entire/metadata@abc123def456\\\"\\n    36→\\tSourceRefTrailerKey = \\\"Entire-Source-Ref\\\"\\n    37→\\n    38→\\t// CheckpointTrailerKey links commits to their checkpoint metadata on entire/checkpoints/v1.\\n    39→\\t// Format: 12 hex characters e.g. \\\"a3b2c4d5e6f7\\\"\\n    40→\\t// This trailer survives git amend and rebase operations.\\n    41→\\tCheckpointTrailerKey = \\\"Entire-Checkpoint\\\"\\n    42→\\n    43→\\t// EphemeralBranchTrailerKey identifies the shadow branch that a checkpoint originated from.\\n    44→\\t// Used in manual-commit strategy checkpoint commits on entire/checkpoints/v1 branch.\\n    45→\\t// Format: full branch name e.g. \\\"entire/2b4c177\\\"\\n    46→\\tEphemeralBranchTrailerKey = \\\"Ephemeral-branch\\\"\\n    47→\\n    48→\\t// AgentTrailerKey identifies the agent that created a checkpoint.\\n    49→\\t// Format: human-readable agent name e.g. \\\"Claude Code\\\", \\\"Cursor\\\"\\n    50→\\tAgentTrailerKey = \\\"Entire-Agent\\\"\\n    51→)\\n    52→\\n    53→// Pre-compiled regexes for trailer parsing.\\n    54→var (\\n    55→\\t// Trailer parsing regexes.\\n    56→\\tstrategyTrailerRegex     = regexp.MustCompile(StrategyTrailerKey + `:\\\\s*(.+)`)\\n    57→\\tmetadataTrailerRegex     = regexp.MustCompile(MetadataTrailerKey + `:\\\\s*(.+)`)\\n    58→\\ttaskMetadataTrailerRegex = regexp.MustCompile(MetadataTaskTrailerKey + `:\\\\s*(.+)`)\\n    59→\\tbaseCommitTrailerRegex   = regexp.MustCompile(BaseCommitTrailerKey + `:\\\\s*([a-f0-9]{40})`)\\n    60→\\tcondensationTrailerRegex = regexp.MustCompile(CondensationTrailerKey + `:\\\\s*(.+)`)\\n    61→\\tsessionTrailerRegex      = regexp.MustCompile(SessionTrailerKey + `:\\\\s*(.+)`)\\n    62→\\tcheckpointTrailerRegex   = regexp.MustCompile(CheckpointTrailerKey + `:\\\\s*(` + checkpointID.Pattern + `)(?:\\\\s|$)`)\\n    63→)\\n    64→\\n    65→// ParseStrategy extracts strategy from commit message.\\n    66→// Returns the strategy name and true if found, empty string and false otherwise.\\n    67→func ParseStrategy(commitMessage string) (string, bool) {\\n    68→\\tmatches := strategyTrailerRegex.FindStringSubmatch(commitMessage)\\n    69→\\tif len(matches) > 1 {\\n    70→\\t\\treturn strings.TrimSpace(matches[1]), true\\n    71→\\t}\\n    72→\\treturn \\\"\\\", false\\n    73→}\\n 