dCheckpointInHistory`:\\n    45→- Use `ParseAllCheckpoints()` instead of `ParseCheckpoint()`\\n    46→- The HEAD fast-path and history walk both collect all IDs from the first matching commit\\n    47→- Empty-check becomes `len(result.checkpointIDs) == 0`\\n    48→\\n    49→### 3. Resume Flow (`resume.go`)\\n    50→\\n    51→Single-checkpoint path (common case) stays identical — no behavior change. When `len(checkpointIDs) == 1`, the existing `resumeSession` flow is used.\\n    52→\\n    53→New `resumeMultipleCheckpoints` function for squash merge commits:\\n    54→1. Gets metadata branch tree (with remote fallback)\\n    55→2. Loops over checkpoint IDs, calling `ReadCheckpointMetadata` + `strat.RestoreLogsOnly` for each\\n    56→3. Skips checkpoints whose metadata isn't available (best-effort)\\n    57→4. Aggregates all restored sessions into a single slice\\n    58→5. Sorts by `CreatedAt` and displays resume commands\\n    59→\\n    60→Output matches existing multi-session format:\\n    61→```\\n    62→Restored 2 sessions. To continue, run:\\n    63→  claude --resume abc123  # implement random_letter script\\n    64→  claude --resume def456  # add random color (most recent)\\n    65→```\\n    66→\\n    67→## Scope\\n    68→\\n    69→### In scope\\n    70→- `trailers/trailers.go` — new `ParseAllCheckpoints()` function\\n    71→- `resume.go` — updated `branchCheckpointResult`, `findBranchCheckpoint`, `findCheckpointInHistory`, new `resumeMultipleCheckpoints`\\n    72→- Tests for all changed code\\n    73→\\n    74→### Out of scope\\n    75→- Dashboard visibility (separate concern)\\n    76→- Handling stripped/customized squash commit messages (best-effort: we work with available trailers)\\n    77→- Branch-not-found error messaging (keep existing behavior)\\n    78→- Changes to condensation, hooks, or checkpoint storage format\\n    79→\\n    80→## Edge Cases\\n    81→\\n    82→- **User customizes squash message and removes trailers**: Best effort — we can only find